that it was ≤£30,000. With the 'complete case data' the probabilities were 80% 
and 90% respectively.
CONCLUSION: This pragmatic randomised trial involving one of the oldest 
populations subjected to a cost-utility analysis, suggests that use of oral 
nutritional supplements in care homes are cost-effective relative to dietary 
advice.

